page.content: {2.WOODLAND}There are deciduos, coniferous and mixed woods in the area. None of them very large, some are natural and ancient and some are man made and fairly recent. The animal life tends to be made up of foxes, badgers, red squirrels and various woodland birds. The coniferous woods are used for commercial purposes and have few ground plants because of the darkness caused by the closely planted trees. The deciduous woods have many plants including - ragged robin, bluebells, primroses and various types of fern.
